[[File:Colantonio.jpg|thumb|350px]]
'''''Saint Jerome in His Study''''' is a c.1445-1446 painting by [[Colantonio]], a painter active in Naples between 1440 and around 1470. It shows the strong influence of contemporary Flemish and French art on the painter and originally formed part of a multi-panel altarpiece for the church of [[San Lorenzo Maggiore, Naples|San Lorenzo Maggiore]], later split up. The work is now in the [[National Museum of Capodimonte]].

